}}
</ref>。

=== 隨機行李檢查 ===
在2008年10月27日，捷運警察宣佈了立即實施隨機檢查背包、皮夾及其他行李的計畫，乘客在上公車和進入地鐵站之前會受到警方隨機抽檢<ref>{{cite news| author = Lena H. Sun| title = Metro to Randomly Search Riders' Bags| url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/27/AR2008102700767.html| work = The Washington Post| page = A01| date = 2008-10-28| accessdate = 2010-02-04| archive-date = 2016-12-23| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161223042516/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/27/AR2008102700767.html| dead-url = no}}</ref>。交通局宣稱美國聯邦第二巡迴上訴法院（United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit）在MacWade v. Kelly的支持下在[[紐約地鐵|紐約地鐵]]實施行李抽檢的決定，是允許華盛頓捷運警察採取類似措施的<ref>Appeals court decision: {{cite web |url=http://www.aele.org/law/2006LRSEP/macwade-kelly.html |title=Brendan MacWade and four other Plaintiffs v. Raymond Kelly, Defendant |last=Brieant |first=Charles L. |authorlink=Charles L. Brieant |coauthors=Newman and Straub, Circuit Judges |date=2006-08-11 |work=www.aele.org |publisher=Americans for Effective Law Enforcement |accessdate=2009-11-07 |archive-date=2016-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223172651/http://www.aele.org/law/2006LRSEP/macwade-kelly.html |dead-url=no }} Original complaint: {{cite web |url=http://news.findlaw.com/hdocs/docs/nyc/mcwadenyc80405cmp.pdf |format=PDF |title=MacWade v. Kelly |author=New York Civil Liberties Foundation |date=2005-08-04 |work=findlaw.com |publisher=[[FindLaw|FindLaw]] |accessdate=2009-11-07 |archive-date=2006-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060119002154/http://news.findlaw.com/hdocs/docs/nyc/mcwadenyc80405cmp.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmata.com/about_metro/news/faqs/preview.cfm?faqID=50|title=News Q & A: MTPD Security Inspection Program|publisher=WMATA|accessdate=2009-01-27|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615182831/http://www.wmata.com/about_metro/news/faqs/preview.cfm?faqID=50|archivedate=2011-06-15}}</ref>。然而安全專家[[布魯斯·施奈爾|布魯斯·施奈爾]]卻認為這項計畫是「用高調卻無實際效用的措施，來防範電影情節中才會出現的威脅」，暗示了他本人懷疑行李抽檢的措施是否真有改善安全的效用<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/discussion/2008/10/30/DI2008103003705.html|title=Bruce Schneier Talks Metro Bag Searches|date=2008-10-31|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=2009-01-27|archive-date=2012-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107043710/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/discussion/2008/10/30/DI2008103003705.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

地鐵乘客諮詢委員會（Metro's Riders'Advisory Council）建議華盛頓都會交通局的董事會至少舉行一次公開會議來考慮這項抽檢計畫。自2008年12月起，交通局仍未執行過一次行李抽檢<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/12/06/AR2008120601866.html|title=Discussion Overdue On Metrorail’s Bag-Search Policy|author=Dr. Gridlock|date=2008-12-07|work=The Washington Post|page=C02|accessdate=2010-02-04|archive-date=2016-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822113954/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/12/06/AR2008120601866.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 重大事故 ==
華盛頓地鐵以發生過數次嚴重的、導致傷亡的撞車事故，也發生過數次造成少數人或無人受傷的出軌意外，交通局也因忽視安全警告及專家建議而遭致批評。三州組成的委員會負責審查華府交通局，但卻沒有監督權。地鐵的安全部門通常負責調查事故成因，但卻無法要求地鐵其他部門提供建議。<ref name="safetywarnings">{{cite news |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/06/05/AR2005060500968.html |title=Safety Warnings Often Ignored at Metro |work=The Washington Post |date=2005-06-06 |last=Becker |first=Jo |coauthors=Lyndsey Layton |accessdate=2009-06-25 |archive-date=2012-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108093605/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/06/05/AR2005060500968.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

